statement.p:
Solve the following system using augmented matrix methods:
\begin{array}{c}
3 x  - 6 y = 6
\\
-6 x + 12 y = -12
\end{array}

p.me:
A + B^T=\left(\begin{array}{cc} 
            a_{11} \amp  a_{12} \cr
	    a_{21} \amp  a_{22} 
	   \end{array}\right)

A - B + C^T=\left(\begin{array}{cc} 
            c_{11} \amp  c_{12} \cr
	    c_{21} \amp  c_{22}
	   \end{array}\right)

A^T B^T=\left(\begin{array}{cc} 
            c_{11} \amp  c_{12} \cr
	    c_{21} \amp  c_{22} 
	   \end{array}\right)

A^{-1}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc} 
            a_{11} \amp  a_{12} \amp  a_{13} \cr
	    a_{21} \amp  a_{22} \amp  a_{23} \cr 
	    a_{31} \amp  a_{32} \amp  a_{33}
	    \end{array}\right)

